---
import MainLayout from '../../layouts/MainLayout.astro';
---

<MainLayout
  title="Autonomous Boat Senior Design Project"
  description="Led a multidisciplinary engineering team in the development of an autonomous boat platform for a collegiate engineering competition."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">Projects</p>

    <h1>Autonomous Boat Senior Design Project</h1>

    <p class="intro">
      Led a multidisciplinary team of mechanical, electrical, and software
      engineers in the development of an autonomous boat platform designed to
      navigate a predetermined course using onboard sensors and computer vision.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Overview</h2>

    <p>
      As the team leader for a multidisciplinary senior design project, I
      managed the development of an autonomous boat intended to navigate a
      predetermined course using onboard sensors, computer vision, and
      autonomous control systems. The project involved mechanical, electrical,
      and software engineering disciplines working together to create a
      functional autonomous platform.
    </p>

    <p>
      While the team's long-term objective was fully autonomous navigation, the
      project was developed incrementally through a series of milestones. By the
      conclusion of the project, the boat was capable of remote-controlled
      operation and successfully demonstrated buoy detection and environmental
      mapping capabilities.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>My Contributions</h2>

    <ul>
      <li>Led a multidisciplinary team consisting of two mechanical engineers, two electrical engineers, and one software engineer</li>
      <li>Defined project scope, milestones, and development priorities</li>
      <li>Planned and facilitated team meetings to coordinate project activities</li>
      <li>Tracked task ownership, progress, and deadlines across all disciplines</li>
      <li>Resolved technical and scheduling challenges to keep the project moving forward</li>
      <li>Coordinated testing logistics, including scheduling and reserving university pool facilities</li>
      <li>Assisted with boat assembly, repairs, waterproofing improvements, and system integration</li>
      <li>Supported software development efforts involving computer vision and buoy recognition</li>
      <li>Helped evaluate design decisions using calculations, testing results, and technical discussions</li>
      <li>Managed team transitions after replacing a team member during the project</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Process</h2>

    <p>
      The project required coordination between multiple engineering disciplines
      working on interconnected systems. Responsibilities included propulsion,
      electrical systems, computer vision, navigation software, and mechanical
      integration. As team leader, I was responsible for ensuring that work
      across these areas remained aligned with project goals and development
      timelines.
    </p>

    <p>
      In addition to project management responsibilities, I participated in the
      technical development of the platform. This included repairing and
      preparing the boat hull, improving waterproofing, integrating mechanical
      systems, supporting propulsion development, and assisting with computer
      vision efforts used to identify colored buoys within the competition
      environment.
    </p>

    <p>
      Throughout the project, technical decisions were guided by engineering
      calculations, testing results, and collaborative discussions among team
      members. Challenges included coordinating schedules, maintaining progress
      across multiple disciplines, and adapting to changes in team composition
      while continuing to meet project milestones.
    </p>

    <p>
      One of the most valuable lessons gained from the project was learning that
      effective leadership extends beyond assigning tasks and enforcing
      deadlines. Team members respond differently to responsibilities and
      challenges, making it important to understand what each person needs to be
      successful. Supporting team members, removing obstacles, and creating an
      environment where people can contribute effectively proved to be just as
      important as technical decision-making.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Tools Used</h2>

    <p>
      Project Leadership • Systems Integration • Team Coordination • MATLAB •
      Computer Vision • Mechanical Assembly • Prototype Testing
    </p>
  </section>
</MainLayout>

